         This blatent support of Wizards is haressy. You should all be burned at the stake!</P><P>First off, Manaburn is wrong. Anyone that thinks one group killing epic mobs is reasonable is a self centered arrogant prick. This game has gone 3 years without being that easy. The people that like manaburn are the same kind of people that enjoy exploiting game bugs so they get an easy ride. Go play progress quest if you're such a loser and a failure.</P><P><b>That all being said, the post was a blatent hoax. All the wizards that fell for it are making me roflmao.</b></P><P>Lifeburn and Manaburn have four differences. One uses the current life, the other uses the current mana. One regenerates part of the lost component with a DoT buff, the other is missing this feature. One can be Crit'd, the other is missing this feature. One costs 9 AA points, the other costs 6 AA points.</P><P>Now lets put these on a scale and balance them out. 3x damage, 3 AA points less, and no danger to the caster; versus regening part of the lost component. I'd say Manaburn is easily 3x better than lifeburn, at less cost.</P><P>But we already know all this, the only real debate is, should wizards have an AA ability 3x better than our AA ability? We certainly don't have any AA abilities that come anywhere close to it.</P><P>Bottom line is, even if they nerfed Manaburn, it would still be better than Lifeburn, and no Wizard will ever get a shread of sympathy from me.</P><P></P><P><BR>Warlock<BR>Shadow Council<BR>Terris-Thule<BR><a href="http://www.shadowcouncil.com" target="_blank">http://www.shadowcouncil.com</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6164" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6164</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
